meta-zybo-z7-10
================

This layer provides board support for the Digilent Zybo Z7-10 board.
It is intended for Yocto/PetaLinux based builds targeting the AMD Xilinx
Zynq-7000 SoC used on Zybo Z7-10.

The layer currently contains:

- A machine configuration for `zybo-z7-10`
- A local XSA integration for the XSCT based flow
- A custom Digilent Linux kernel recipe based on `linux-xlnx`
- An initial BSP-based device tree customization layer


Dependencies
============

This layer depends on the following Yocto layers being available in the build:

- `poky/meta`
  Core OpenEmbedded metadata required by all builds.

- `meta-xilinx/meta-xilinx-core`
  Provides the Xilinx machine infrastructure and the base `linux-xlnx`
  kernel include used by this layer.

- `meta-xilinx-tools`
  Provides the `external-hdf` recipe used to import the local
  `system.xsa` hardware description into the build.

- `meta-petalinux`
  Required when using the XSCT based PetaLinux style flow enabled by this
  layer configuration.

At the layer metadata level, `conf/layer.conf` declares only `core` as a
formal dependency. In practice, the machine and kernel content in this layer
also rely on the Xilinx and PetaLinux layers listed above.


Contents
========

- `conf/machine/zybo-z7-10.conf`
  Machine definition for the Zybo Z7-10 board.

- `files/zybo-z7-10/system.xsa`
  Local hardware handoff archive used by the XSCT flow.
  This file is taken from the Digilent Zybo Z7-10 PetaLinux BSP.

- `recipes-bsp/hdf/external-hdf_%.bbappend`
  Extends `external-hdf` so the XSA can be fetched from this layer.

- `recipes-bsp/device-tree/device-tree.bbappend`
  Extends the `device-tree` recipe so board-specific DTSI files can be
  supplied from this layer.

- `recipes-bsp/device-tree/files/system-user.dtsi`
  Initial BSP-derived device tree customization applied on top of the
  generated base device tree.

- `recipes-kernel/linux/linux-xlnx-digilent_5.15_v2022.1.bb`
  Custom kernel recipe using Digilent's `linux-digilent` source tree.


Adding The Layer
================

Add the layer to `bblayers.conf`:

  bitbake-layers add-layer ../sources/meta-zybo-z7-10

Then select the machine in `local.conf`:

  MACHINE ??= "zybo-z7-10"


Notes
=====

- The current kernel recipe is based on Digilent's 5.15 kernel branch.
- The hardware platform is supplied from `system.xsa` stored in this layer,
  rather than fetched from an external URL.
- The device tree flow currently uses the generated base device tree plus
  `system-user.dtsi` from this layer for board-specific customizations.
- This layer is compatible with the `scarthgap` Yocto release series.
